<p class="lead">In this section, you will learn the basics about managing files and folders and using them to organize information that you wish to save on your computer.</p>

<h6><i>This is important for two reasons.</i></h6>

<br />
								


									<p><strong>Computers are machines. </strong> <br />They follow instructions - either the instructions you enter in to the machine or the instructions already programmed into it. If you do not tell the computer where you want information stored, it will store it according to default locations. As an empowered computer user, you control the information stored within it and tell the computer where you want the information to go. You will learn how in this section.</p>

<br />
							<p><Strong>Computers and their programs are organized in a particular way.</strong> <br /> As you learned in Computer Basics, understanding just how and why files and folders on the computer are organized gives you knowledge beyond just knowing how to use them. This knowledge empowers you over the computer and its programs so you can use them more effectively.</p>
																<p>This and the previous section, "Computer Basics" are the <strong>most misunderstood</strong>, even for those who already use a computer, so take your time and work carefully. Remember, you can go through each section or just the ones you think you need. It is your choice.</p>
